# Conversation Modes Documentation

Applies when editing `src/chat/conversation-modes/**`. Reference implementation: legacy `src/chat/compose-system-prompt.ts`.

## Catalog vs prompt bodies

- **Catalog metadata** (`*/mode-description.ts`, `ConversationModeMeta`) — student-facing labels for GET `/api/chat/conversation-modes`. Never include LLM prompt text.
- **Prompt sections** (`teaching-methodology.ts`, etc.) — system or user-turn LLM instructions. Never exposed via the catalog API.

## File header

2–3 sentences: purpose, when used, cross-ref to related modules. No empty trailing `*` lines.

## Exported types

One-liner above each exported type/interface. Property docs on interfaces shared across modules (e.g. `SystemPromptBuildContext`).

## Exported functions

Summary + behavioral note + `@param` + `@returns`. Add `@throws` when validation throws. Use `{@link TypeName}` for mode IDs and context types.

## Classes

Class block listing responsibilities. JSDoc on public/abstract methods callers override or invoke.

## Prompt constants

File header must state:
1. LLM prompt body (not API catalog)
2. Which `ConversationModePromptModule` id injects it (if system prompt)
3. Which mode class returns it

Do not add JSDoc on the string literal itself.

## Private helpers

Undocumented unless non-obvious (see `00-kernel.mdc`).

## New modes

When adding `explanatory/` or future modes, follow the same pattern as `socratic/`.
